          "type": "tool_result",
          "tool_use_id": "call_13_IfdpKdIZSRwSTgpPPaj27058",
          "content": "# 猫咪舔蜜柑汁液安全\r\n对话ID: 111f8fe8-bc39-4835-ba82-0130b54aeaae\r\n创建时间: 2026-03-31T11:17:12.500000+08:00\r\n更新时间: 2026-03-31T14:47:13.725000+08:00\r\n\r\n## ❓ unknown\r\n\r\n猫咪可以吃柑橘吗？我吃了蜜柑手上有一些残留的汁液被猫咪舔了会中毒吗？\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## ❓ unknown\r\n\r\n{'type': 'SEARCH', 'results': [{'url': 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2180184/#:~:text=Cats%20are%20susceptible%20to%20poisoning,ataxia%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20hypothermia.', 'title': 'Toxicology of selected pesticides, drugs, and chemicals. D-limonene, linalool, and crude citrus oil extracts - PubMed', 'snippet': 'S B Hooser. ... Cats are susceptible to poisoning by insecticidal products containing D-limonene, linalool, and crude citrus oil extracts. Signs of toxicosis include hypersalivation, muscle tremors, ataxia, depression, and hypothermia.', 'cite_index': 1, 'published_at': None, 'site_name': 'National Institutes of Health (NIH) | (.gov)', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/nih.gov', 'query_indexes': [0, 1], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://www.anti-a.org/news/tw/food-that-cats-and-dogs-cant-eat', 'title': '飼主快看！貓狗不能吃的地雷食物 1水果「狗可以貓不行」 — Anti Additive Clean Label Organization', 'snippet': '狗狗可以吃少量，貓咪請避免！柑橘類含有D-檸檬酸及柑橘精油，貓狗接觸後會出現過敏及中毒反應，除此之外，家長也要留意常見產品包括洗碗精、精油或殺蟲劑等，都含有柑橘精油或相關成分，在使用時別讓貓咪靠近、誤食喔！', 'cite_index': 2, 'published_at': 1659024000.0, 'site_name': 'Anti Additive Clean Label Organization', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/anti-a.org', 'query_indexes': [4], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34824643/', 'title': 'Safety and efficacy of feed additives consisting of expressed sweet orange peel oil and its fractions from Citrus sinensis (L.) Osbeck for use in all animal species (FEFANA asbl) - PubMed', 'snippet': '2021 Nov 19;19(11):e06891. ... For dogs, cats, ornamental fish ... no conclusion can be drawn. For the other species, the FEEDAP Panel concluded that the additives under assessment are safe at the maximum proposed use levels in complete feed.', 'cite_index': 3, 'published_at': 1637251200.0, 'site_name': 'National Institutes of Health (NIH) | (.gov)', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/nih.gov', 'query_indexes': [0], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://popline.org/node/312923', 'title': 'An evaluation of the acute toxicity of an insecticidal spray containing linalool, d-limonene, and piperonyl butoxide applied topically to domestic cats', 'snippet': 'A study was conducted to evaluate the toxicity to the cat of a citrus extract-based insecticidal product, a ready-to-use spray-can formulation containing d-limonene and linalool, the synergist piperonyl butoxide and a fragrance (D-8364) in propylene glycol and ethanol. One cat each was treated (i.e.', 'cite_index': 4, 'published_at': None, 'site_name': 'EurekaMag', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/popline.org', 'query_indexes': [1], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35137417/', 'title': 'Incidence of Vitis fruit-induced clinical signs and acute kidney injury in dogs and cats - PubMed', 'snippet': 'acute kidney injury in dogs and cats M A Dijkman et al. J Small Anim Pract. ... Clinical significance: In this study, a significant proportion (around 15%) of dogs and cats developed clinical signs after ingestion of Vitis fruits, which were predominantly related to the gastrointestinal tract.', 'cite_index': 5, 'published_at': 1644249600.0, 'site_name': 'National Institutes of Health (NIH) | (.gov)', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/nih.gov', 'query_indexes': [0], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://www.miamiherald.com/living/article299599184.html#storylink=moresection', 'title': 'Why Do Cats Hate Orange Peel? Vets Explain', 'snippet': 'Nita Vasudevan, veterinarian at Embrace Pet Insurance told Newsweek that cats are often repelled by the smell of oranges and other citrus fruits because their peel contains compounds called limonene and linalool, which are very strong-smelling to feline noses.', 'cite_index': 6, 'published_at': 1738425600.0, 'site_name': 'Miami Herald', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/miamiherald.com', 'query_indexes': [1], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://search.tradmedlibrary.org/tmgl/?lang=en&q=mh%3A%22Citrus%2Fpoisoning%22', 'title': 'Search', 'snippet': 'ABSTRACT Cats are susceptible to poisoning by insecticidal products containing D-limonene, linalool, and crude citrus oil extracts. Signs of toxicosis include hypersalivation, muscle tremors, ataxia, depression, and hypothermia.', 'cite_index': 7, 'published_at': 1456761600.0, 'site_name': 'tradmedlibrary.org', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/tradmedlibrary.org', 'query_indexes': [1], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://kepuah.cn/show.htm?method=show_focus&id=10071', 'title': '科普安徽', 'snippet': '其实让猫咪反应如此强烈的气味并不仅限于柑橘类水果，还有柠檬，樟脑丸，膏药，牙膏，风油精，醋，香水等等。这其中的一大原因就是猫咪拥有非常敏锐的嗅觉。', 'cite_index': 8, 'published_at': 1650729600.0, 'site_name': '科普安徽', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/kepuah.cn', 'query_indexes': [1], 'is_hidden': False}, {'url': 'https://www.sigmaaldrich.cn/CN/zh/search/w263516?focus=papers&page=1&perpage=30&sort=relevance&term=W263516&type=citation_search', 'title': 'W263516', 'snippet': '关键词:\\'W263516\\'  显示 1-30 #N/A 48 条结果 关于 \"W263516\" 范围 论文  The Veterinary clinics of North America. Small animal practice, 20(2), 383-385 (1990-03-01)  Cats are susceptible to poisoning by insecticidal pr', 'cite_index': 9, 'published_at': None, 'site_name': '默克生命科学', 'site_icon': 'https://cdn.deepseek.com/site-icons/sigmaaldrich.cn', 'query_indexes': [1], 'is_hidden': False}]}\r\n嗯，用户吃了蜜柑后手上有汁液被猫舔了，很担心会不会中毒。这其实是个很常见的小意外场景，用户需要的是一个明确的、能让人安心的判断，同时也想了解背后的原理。\r\n\r\n我计划先给出核心结论让用户放心，然后解释为什么残留汁液风险不大，再告诉用户需要注意观察什么症状作为安全底线，最后补充相关知识帮助用户未来避免类似情况。\r\n\r\n来看搜索结果的质量。有个来自NIH的PubMed文献明确指出猫对D-柠檬烯和芳樟醇敏感，中毒症状包括流口水、肌肉震颤、共济失调等[citation:1][citation:7]，这是权威的学术来源。还有2025年兽医的科普解读很有价值[citation:6]，直接点出需要大量摄入才会严重中毒，且果肉比果皮安全。Miami Herald虽然不算顶级学术来源，但内容引用了多位兽医的明确观点，时效性也好，可以采用。\r\n\r\n关于柑橘类有毒性的结论，有个组织网站也明确说猫要避免柑橘类[citation:2]，提到D-柠檬酸和柑橘精油。还有EFSA的饲料添加剂安全评估[citation:3]讨论柑橘油在动物饲料中的使用，来自官方机构，权威性高。另有关于高浓度杀虫剂喷雾对猫影响的研究[citation:4]，虽然涉及柑橘提取物浓度较高，但能印证过量才会有明显症状。\r\n\r\n有几个搜索结果不太相关，比如葡萄对猫狗肾脏损伤的研究[citation:5]和科普安徽讲猫咪嗅觉敏感的内容[citation:8]，后者虽然有价值但权威性一般。默克生命科学那页[citation:9]内容杂乱，主要引用的是PubMed已有信息。\r\n\r\n综合这些信息，我会先明确告知用户少量残留汁液不会中毒，解释毒性物质主要浓缩在果皮精油中，手上残留量极少。然后列出需要警惕的症状清单供用户观察，包括流口水、呕吐、精神变差、震颤等[citation:1][citation:6][citation:7]。最后补充说明整颗蜜柑包括果皮和种子对猫有风险，让用户未来注意不要主动喂食。\r\n\r\n考虑到用户可能在手机端阅读，我会避免使用表格，用清晰的小标题和简洁的段落来组织信息，让用户快速获取关键结论和行动建议。\r\n别担心，你手上残留的少量蜜柑汁液被猫咪舔到，**通常不会引起严重中毒**，但建议你观察一下猫咪的状态。\r\n\r\n猫咪对柑橘类水果的厌恶是刻在基因里的自我保护[citation:8]，但微量接触和**食用**是两回事：\r\n\r\n*   **毒性来源**：危险成分主要是**D-柠檬烯**和**芳樟醇**，高浓度集中在果皮精油里，果肉含量较低[citation:1][citation:2][citation:6]。\r\n*   **剂量问题**：你手上残留的这点汁液，剂量远未达到危险线。通常需要大量摄入果皮或高浓度精油才会中毒[citation:4][citation:6]。\r\n*   **潜在反应**：**流口水、轻微呕吐**是最常见的，因为味道太刺激[citation:1][citation:6]。极少数敏感猫咪可能**精神变差或发抖**[citation:1][citation:2]。\r\n\r\n### 🐱 接下来可以这样做\r\n为了安全起见，可以做好这几点：\r\n\r\n1.  **观察症状**：接下来的几小时，留意有没有**流口水、呕吐、腹泻**，或者精神不好、动作不稳、发抖。\r\n2.  **鼓励喝水**：让猫咪喝点水，帮助稀释咽下去的汁液，冲淡味道。\r\n3.  **及时就医**：如果出现**频繁呕吐、精神萎靡或明显发抖**，就尽快送医。\r\n\r\n**虽然手上汁液问题不大，但整个蜜柑（尤其是皮和籽）对猫是有风险的，以后一定放好别让猫偷吃。** 不过如果只是舔了手上的残留，放宽心，大概率没事。\r\n\r\n---"
